aas_core.aas3_0.types.model

Interface ISubmodelElementList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IClass, IHasDataSpecification, IHasExtensions, IHasSemantics, IQualifiable, IReferable, ISubmodelElement
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EnhancedSubmodelElementList, SubmodelElementList

    public interface ISubmodelElementList
extends ISubmodelElement
    A submodel element list is an ordered list of submodel elements.

    The numbering starts with zero (0).

    Constraints:

    • Constraint AASd-107: If a first level child element in a SubmodelElementList has a IHasSemantics.getSemanticId() it shall be identical to getSemanticIdListElement().
    • Constraint AASd-114: If two first level child elements in a SubmodelElementList have a IHasSemantics.getSemanticId() then they shall be identical.
    • Constraint AASd-115: If a first level child element in a SubmodelElementList does not specify a IHasSemantics.getSemanticId() then the value is assumed to be identical to getSemanticIdListElement().
    • Constraint AASd-120: The IReferable.getIdShort() of a ISubmodelElement being a direct child of a SubmodelElementList shall not be specified.
    • Constraint AASd-108: All first level child elements in a SubmodelElementList shall have the same submodel element type as specified in getTypeValueListElement().
    • Constraint AASd-109: If getTypeValueListElement() is equal to AasSubmodelElements.PROPERTY or AasSubmodelElements.RANGE getValueTypeListElement() shall be set and all first level child elements in the SubmodelElementList shall have the value type as specified in getValueTypeListElement().
